OL,3,CHome Office 'wasted' #15m of
OL,4,Ctaxpayers' cash on migrant camp
OL,6,FThe Home Office spent #15 million
OL,7,Fbuying a derelict prison contaminated
OL,8,Fwith asbestos amid political pressure
OL,9,Fto stop housing migrants in hotels,
OL,10,Faccording to Whitehall's spending
OL,11,Fwatchdog.
OL,13,FThe government department cut corners
OL,14,Fand paid more than it needed to in its
OL,15,Fhaste to acquire the Northeye site in
OL,16,FBexhill-on-Sea, East Sussex, but this
OL,17,Fwas "ultimately deemed unfit for its
OL,18,Fintended purpose due to
OL,19,Fcontamination", the National Audit
OL,20,FOffice (NAO) said.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G1/18
