OL,3,CHome Office 'wasted' #15m of
OL,4,Ctaxpayers' cash on migrant camp
OL,6,FCampaigners said millions of pounds of
OL,7,Fpublic money was "thrown away on a
OL,8,Fcontaminated and dangerous site that
OL,9,Fshould never have been under
OL,10,Fconsideration" as they branded the
OL,11,Frevelations a "fiasco".
OL,13,FThe chairman of a Commons committee
OL,14,Fwhich scrutinises government spending
OL,15,Fcriticised the Home Office for "rushed
OL,16,Fand misjudged" decision making which
OL,17,Fresulted in "overpaying" for a site
OL,18,Fwhich was "not fit for purpose" and
OL,19,Fsaid MPs would make sure taxpayers'
OL,20,Fcash was not "wasted in future
OL,21,Facquisitions".
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G3/18
